docs.abstract: Internet-based retailers, especially Amazon, have had a particularly devastating impact on electronics retailers, many of whom have struggled to adapt to the technological age they helped usher in.
docs.snippet: Internet-based retailers, especially Amazon, have had a particularly devastating impact on electronics retailers, many of whom have struggled to adapt to the technological age they helped usher in.
docs.lead_paragraph: I was assembling a home audio system recently and needed speaker wires. A friend recommended RadioShack. I went to two — in Manhattan and in Brooklyn — but, to my surprise, neither carried any. How could RadioShack, the place Americans go to for cables, connectors, circuits and all kinds of other electronic doodads, not have speaker wires?

docs.abstract: Amazon has hired Mr. Carney as senior vice president for global corporate affairs. The move is unusual, as Amazon is known for grooming employees from within.
docs.snippet: Amazon has hired Mr. Carney as senior vice president for global corporate affairs. The move is unusual, as Amazon is known for grooming employees from within.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon, a technology company obsessed with secrecy, is hiring a former press secretary for President Obama, whose administration has been widely criticized for its aggressive leak investigations.

headline.main: Amazon Hires Jay Carney, Former Obama Press Secretary
headline.print_headline: Former Obama Press Secretary Is Hired by Amazon in New Post

docs.abstract: A soon-to-start online marketplace that aims to loosen Amazon’s grip on e-commerce raises $140 million.
docs.snippet: A soon-to-start online marketplace that aims to loosen Amazon’s grip on e-commerce raises $140 million.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jet.com, a soon-to-start online marketplace that aims to loosen Amazon’s grip on e-commerce, said Wednesday that it had raised $140 million in a new round of funding.

docs.abstract: Proposed regulations requiring daylight flights with craft always being kept in sight might ground planned delivery services like Amazon’s Prime Air.
docs.snippet: Proposed regulations requiring daylight flights with craft always being kept in sight might ground planned delivery services like Amazon’s Prime Air.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an attempt to bring order to increasingly chaotic skies, the Federal Aviation Administration on Sunday proposed long-awaited rules on the commercial use of small drones, requiring operators to be certified, fly only during daylight and keep their aircraft in sight.

headline.main: F.A.A. Rules Would Limit Commercial Drone Use
headline.print_headline: F.A.A. Acts to Regulate Drones Used for Business

docs.abstract: Amazon’s television production wing ordered full seasons of its pilot programs for “The Man in the High Castle,” “Mad Dogs,” “The New Yorker Presents,” “Just Add Magic” and “The Stinky & Dirty Show.”
docs.snippet: Amazon’s television production wing ordered full seasons of its pilot programs for “The Man in the High Castle,” “Mad Dogs,” “The New Yorker Presents,” “Just Add Magic” and “The Stinky & Dirty Show.”
docs.lead_paragraph: In January, Amazon Studios, the online retail giant’s television production wing, posted 10 original pilots for viewers to watch and vote on. This morning, five of them were ordered to series: “The Man in the High Castle,” based on the Philip K. Dick novel that imagines an alternate reality in which the Axis powers won World War II; “Mad Dogs,” a dark comedy executive produced by Shawn Ryan (“The Shield,” “Terriers”); “The New Yorker Presents,” a docu-series overseen by Alex Gibney (“Taxi To the Dark Side,” “We Steal Secrets”); and the kids series “Just Add Magic” and “The Stinky & Dirty Show.”

headline.main: Amazon Orders Full Seasons for Five New Shows
headline.print_headline: Five Series Coming From Amazon Studios

docs.abstract: Based on Michael Connelly’s series of novels, “Bosch” stars Titus Welliver as a rule-bending Los Angeles detective scarred by a grim childhood.
docs.snippet: Based on Michael Connelly’s series of novels, “Bosch” stars Titus Welliver as a rule-bending Los Angeles detective scarred by a grim childhood.
docs.lead_paragraph: The list of brooding, taciturn small-screen police detectives is already impossibly long, so you might think Amazon made a mistake in committing to “Bosch,” whose title character is yet another variation. But this 10-episode series, which is being rolled out Friday on Amazon Prime, proves gripping nonetheless.

headline.main: Review: ‘Bosch,’ Amazon Prime’s New Crime Series
headline.print_headline: The Maverick Gumshoe, Casually Cutting Corners
